    <instructions>In a preheated 400 degree F oven, toast bread cubes 5 to 7 minutes or until barely golden.

In a large skillet, melt butter and cook onion and celery over medium heat for 3 minutes or until softened. Transfer to a bowl and add bread cubes, herbs, salt, pepper, and chicken broth. Toss well and adjust seasoning.

Transfer to baking dish and bake in Bake at 325 degrees F for 20 minutes until heated through and crust forms on top.</instructions>
